June 25 (Reuters) - Russian President Vladimir Putin and Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko discussed the global fertiliser supply situation at a meeting on Saturday. "I would like to talk to you in terms of meeting global market needs," Putin said in footage from the meeting posted on social media by a reporter from state broadcaster Russia 1. Russia and Belarus are major suppliers of fertiliser to the global market, Putin added. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.